The defendant Kareion Deon Jordan was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Disorderly Conduct [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse Assessments], a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: REQUEST TO ISSUE CIVIL JUDGMENT RECEIVED AND FORWARDED TO ALI. OS

Defendant Kareion Deon Jordan not in court.  Erika Frank Motsch appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy court clerk cmt.
  Per email from Probation Dept., defendant is currently in absconder status.  Court ordered defendant to serve 30 days of the condition time; straight time.  Commitment For Condition Time For Non-Compliance With Probation Conditions - Domestic Violence Court signed and filed.

Defendant Kareion Deon Jordan in court with attorney Gary Edward Rosenthal.  Sarah McNutt appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy court clerk cmt.
Defendant prepared to enter change of plea.  Hearing proceeded. 

Pursuant to plea negotiations and on State's motion,  Court orders Repeater enhancer DISMISSED.  

Negotiations set forth by the state.

As to Count 1 as AMENDED:  Defendant changes his plea to GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to his plea, advised of his Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty.   Defendant advised that if not a United States Citizen, deportation is possible.  Court found that defendant knowingly, voluntarily and intelligently waived his rights.  Guilty Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea.  Court found defendant guilty and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record.

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by parties and the defendant.

The court sentenced the defendant to serve 3 months in the House of Correction, consecutive, with credit for 2 days time served.  The court STAYED sentence and placed defendant on probation with the WI Department of Corrections for a period of 24 months.

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:
-Serve 30 days in the House of Correction STAYED pending a review on 5-13-2016 at 1:30 pm in Branch 45.
-Attend and successfully complete Batterers Intervention.
-AODA and recommended treatment/Maintain ABSOLUTE SOBRIETY.
-Attend and successfully complete treatment and counseling programs as deemed appropriate by agent.
-NO CONTACT with the victim, UNLESS requested by victim and then only with prior approval of agent or the court.
-Obtain/maintain employment.
-No contact with firearms.
-Pay all MANDATORY costs, assessments, surcharges, victim/witness surcharge, domestic violence surcharge, and supervision fees as determined by Dept of Corrections.  Any amount remaining due and owing is subject to civil judgment and/or tax intercept or other means. ANY CASH BAIL ON DEPOSIT TO BE APPLIED.
-Provide DNA sample, pay costs and DNA surcharge.
-Restitution is set at $0.
-48 USC Section 922(g)(9) prohibits possession of a firearm and/or ammunition after conviction of a misdemeanor crime of domestic violence.
